OL,6,FPC Ralph said: "The head was to the
OL,7,Fleft. It was concave, the top of the
OL,8,Fhead.
OL,10,F"That was what we touched. I unwrapped
OL,11,Fit two or three times before I got to
OL,12,Fa part where I could see red pooling.
OL,14,F"A couple of seconds after, we went to
OL,15,Fthe right-hand side. I put my hand
OL,16,Fdown.
OL,18,F"My hand slipped on something. I
OL,19,Flooked and that was the baby's leg. My
OL,20,Fhand was soaking wet."
