OL,6,FFollowing his arrival at Worthing
OL,7,Fpolice station, Gordon was invited to
OL,8,Ftell his "side of the story".
OL,10,FHe got out of a wheelchair and lay on
OL,11,Fthe floor saying his legs were hurting
OL,12,Fand he was "in pain".
OL,14,FLater, he complained he was receiving
OL,15,F"sub-par treatment", saying: "I don't
OL,16,Fthink I should be talked to like I'm a
OL,17,Fnobody.
OL,19,F"I mean I'm a suspect. I have not
OL,20,Fcommitted any crimes, therefore I
OL,21,Fshould have respect.
